refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 stringfalseexec
 stringcommand
 arrayoutput&null;
 intresult_code&null;



 exec executes the given
 command.

&reftitle.errors;
Emits an E_WARNING if exec is unable to fork the command.
Throws a ValueError if command is empty or contain null bytes.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.0.0

     If command is empty or contains null bytes,
     exec now throws a ValueError.
     Previously it emitted an E_WARNING and returned &false;.

  &reftitle.examples;



    An exec example


<?php
// outputs the username that owns the running php/httpd process
// (on a system with the "whoami" executable in the path)
$output=null;
$retval=null;
exec('whoami', $output, $retval);
echo "Returned with status $retval and output:\n";
print_r($output);
?>


    &example.outputs.similar;


Returned with status 0 and output:
Array
(
    [0] => cmb
)
